 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "InspectionAdvisor ⊣ Infrastructure Inspection Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A road/bridge-infrastructure-
 inspection BACK-OFFICE COORDINATION actor for an independent
 inspection contractor -- not direct inspection-robot-actuation
 authority (beyond passive sensing) and not a structure-closure
 authority. Four ops (`:log-inspection` / `:structural-scan` /
 `:escalate-structural-concern` / `:schedule-reinspection`), all
 `:effect :propose` only. Thirteen concrete governor checks:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct hardware/closure control), permanent
 equipment-actuate block, permanent closure-authority side-channel
 block (this actor never self-reports a structure closure outside the
 gated structural-concern-escalation path), independent structure
 verification/registration before any scan or reinspection schedule,
 independent recompute of the acceptable/deficient finding from the
 raw condition-rating sensor reading against the structure's own
 registered maintenance-trigger threshold (never trusting a proposal's
 own self-reported finding), condition-rating plausibility validation
 (scale-aware: 0-9 or 0-100), rating-scale validation, independent
 on-file-deficient-finding gate before any reinspection may be
 scheduled (or billed), double-schedule guard, and survey-type
 validation. A thirteenth, EXTRA check unique to this actor:
 independent recompute of a `:critical?` triage flag grounded in the
 real external scale's own fixed, non-local-discretion boundary --
 FHWA/AASHTO NBIS (23 CFR 650 Subpart C) / Manual for Bridge Evaluation
 condition rating <= 1 ('Imminent Failure', closed to traffic) on the
 0-9 bridge-component scale, or ASTM D6433 Pavement Condition Index
 <= 10 ('Failed', demands immediate reconstruction) on the 0-100
 pavement scale -- cited only for these two verified numeric anchors,
 never for a fabricated maintenance-trigger threshold (that stays the
 operator's own registered value). Structural-concern escalation (a
 defect requiring immediate closure, the exact scenario this README
 names) ALWAYS escalates to a human public-works authority;
 `:log-inspection` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at
 phase 3 when governor-clean."}
